              Express <m>l(x)</m> in terms of <m>f</m> and describe how the graph of <m>y=f(x)</m> can be transformed into the graph of <m>y=l(x)</m>.
            </p>
          </statement>
          <answer>
            <p>
              <m>l(x)=3f(x)</m>. So, we can stretch the graph of <m>y=f(x)</m> vertically by a factor of <m>3</m> to obtain <m>y=l(x)</m>.
            </p>
          </answer>
        </exercise>
